The pilot reported that he was flying his powered parachute at various low altitudes, and that, 
during a climb along a ridgeline, it struck high-voltage transmission power lines less than 100 
feet above ground level. The powered parachute descended to the ground and came to rest 
inverted, substantially damaging its structural tubing. The pilot reported no preimpact 
mechanical failures or malfunctions with the powered parachute that would have precluded 
normal operation.
